Road]] which connects the city with western districts like [[Tiruppur]], [[Coimbatore]] and [[Kerala]]. [[Erode Ring Road]] connecting all the arterial roads of is intersecting [[Perundurai Road, Erode|Perundurai road]] here.It is a developing area due to the initiation of various educational institutions. \n\n==Institutions in and around Thindal==\n\n*[[Vellalar College for Women]] (Government Aided-Autonomous)Since 1970  <ref>https://vcw.ac.in/</ref>\n* [https://velalarengg.ac.in/ Velalar College of Engineering and Technology] <ref>https://velalarengg.ac.in/</ref>\n*[[Vellalar College for Women|vellalar College of Education for Women]]\n* Vellalar [[Matriculation]] Higher Secondary School for Girls Since 1980\n* Vellalar High School for Girls\n* Vellalar Vidyalaya Senior Secondary School (CBSE) <ref>https://velalarcbse.com/</ref>\n* vellalar College of Nursing \n* Vellalar Teacher' Training Institute\n* Govt. High School, Thindal\n* BVB Matric Higher Secondary School, Thindal. <ref>http://thebvb.com/</ref>\n* The BVB(CBSE), Therkku pallam, Thindal.<ref> http://thebvb.com/</ref>\n* URC [[Matriculation]] School <ref>http://www.urcschool.com/</ref>\n* AET Matriculation School\n* The Indian Public School,([[Central Board of Secondary Education|CBSE]]) <ref>https://www.theindianpublicschool.org/</ref>\n* Geethanjanli All India Senior Secondary school - [[Central Board of Secondary Education|CBSE]] <ref>http://geethaanjali.edu.in/</ref>\n* CS Academy -[[Central Board of Secondary Education|CBSE]] (BVB) <ref>https://csacademy.in/</ref>\n\n==Nearby places==\n\nNearby places include [http://texvalleyindia.com/about-texvalley/ Texvalley],<ref>http://texvalleyindia.com/about-texvalley/</ref> [[Gangapuram]] (6&nbsp;km). [[Vellode Birds Sanctuary|Vellode Bird Sanctuary]] (11.5 km), [[Sangameswarar Temple|Bhavani Sangameswarar Temple]] (12.9 km), [[Villarasampatti]] (2.8&nbsp;km), Koorapalayam (5.1&nbsp;km), Ellappalayam (5.1&nbsp;km), Kavundachipalayam (5.9&nbsp;km)\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Erode district]]\n", "name_user": "Sinsen", "label": "safe", "comment": "sentence correction", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thindal,_Erode"}
{"title_page": "Ketapang railway station (Banyuwangi)", "text_new": "{{Infobox station\n | name          = Ketapang Station\n | image         = Stasiun Banyuwangi Baru Malam Hari - panoramio.jpg\n | image_caption = Front view\n | address       = Kalipuro, [[Banyuwangi Regency|Banyuwangi]], [[East Java]]\n | country       = [[Indonesia]]\n | coordinates   ={{coord|8|8|28|S|114|23|50|E|source:nlwiki_type:railwaystation_scale:10000|display=title,inline}}\n | owned         = [[Indonesian Railway Company]]\n | line          = [[Kalisat\u2013Banyuwangi railway|Kalisat\u2013Banyuwangi]]\n | platform      = 3\n | tracks        = 6\n | other         =\n | parking       = Available\n | bicycle       =\n | ADA           = Available\n | code          = Ktg\n | zone          =\n | opened        = 1985\n | rebuilt       =\n | mpassengers   =\n | passengers    =\n | pass_system   =\n | pass_year     =\n | pass_percent  =\n | services      =\n | image_upright = \n | baggage_check =\n | map_type      = Indonesia_Banyuwangi Regency\n | map_caption   = Location in [[Banyuwangi Regency]]\n | elevation     = {{convert|7|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n | native_name   = ''{{smaller|Stasiun Ketapang Banyuwangi}}\n | structure     = Ground\n }}\n'''Ketapang Station''' (formerly '''Banyuwangi Baru Station''' or '''New Banyuwangi Station''') is a railway station, managed by [[Indonesian Railway Company]], located at Kalipuro, [[Banyuwangi Regency]], [[East Java]]. This station is at the most southeastern railway station in [[Asia]].\n\nAs of 1 December 2019, the station was renamed into '''Ketapang Station.'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://kabarrakyat.id/pt-kai-setuju-stasiun-karangasem-banyuwangi-baru-berganti-nama/|title=PT. KAI Setuju Stasiun Karangasem \u2013 Banyuwangi Baru Berganti Nama|last=REDAKSI|date=2019-07-23|website=Kabar Rakyat .id|language=en-US|access-date=2019-11-02}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://news.detik.com/berita-jawa-timur/d-4636646/nama-dua-stasiun-di-banyuwangi-bakal-berganti|title=Nama Dua Stasiun di Banyuwangi Bakal Berganti|last=Fanani|first=Ardian|website=detiknews|access-date=2019-07-24}}</ref>\n\n==Destination==\nThe railway services that use this station :\n\n=== Executive and Business Class ===\n* ''Mutiara Timur'' to [[Surabaya Gubeng railway station|Surabaya Gubeng]]\n\n=== Economy PSO Class ===\n* ''Sri Tanjung'' to [[Lempuyangan railway station|Lempuyangan]]\n* ''Probowangi'' to [[Surabaya Gubeng railway station|Surabaya Gubeng]]\n* ''Tawang Alun'' to [[Malang railway station|Malang]]\n\n=== Local Train ===\n* ''Pandanwangi'' to [[Jember railway station|Jember]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{S-rail-start}}\n{{s-rail|title=Indonesian Railway Company}}\n{{rail line\n|previous = {{stnlnk|Argopuro}}\n|route    = [[Kalisat\u2013Banyuwangi railway|'''<span style=\"color: red\">Kalisat\u2013Banyuwangi</span>''']]\n|next     = ''Terminus''\n|col      = FF0000\n|term1    = {{stnlnk|Kalisat}}\n}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Train Stations in Indonesia|East Java}}\n\n[[Category:Banyuwangi Regency]]\n[[Category:Railway stations in East Java]]\n[[Category:Railway stations opened in 1985]]\n\n\n{{Indonesia-railstation-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox station\n | name          = Ketapang Station\n | image         = Stasiun Banyuwangi Baru Malam Hari - panoramio.jpg\n | image_caption = Front view\n | address       = Kalipuro, [[Banyuwangi Regency|Banyuwangi]], [[East Java]]\n | country       = [[Indonesia]]\n | coordinates   ={{coord|8|8|28|S|114|23|50|E|source:nlwiki_type:railwaystation_scale:10000|display=title,inline}}\n | owned         = [[Indonesian Railway Company]]\n | line          = [[Kalisat\u2013Banyuwangi railway|Kalisat\u2013Banyuwangi]]\n | platform      = 3\n | tracks        = 6\n | other         =\n | parking       = Available\n | bicycle       =\n | ADA           = Available\n | code          = Ktg\n | zone          =\n | opened        = 1985\n | rebuilt       =\n | mpassengers   =\n | passengers    =\n | pass_system   =\n | pass_yea